#### C-3: ProtectedRoute Never Validates Token Expiry

**What:** [protected-route.jsx](file:///d:/Mallakhamb-Repo/Mallakhamb-server-refactor/Web/src/middleware/protected-route.jsx) checks if a token *exists* in storage but never calls `isTokenExpired()`. A user with an expired token gets an infinite loading spinner (lines 41-55, 63-76) because `token && userData` is truthy but `AuthContext.user` is null.

**Why it matters:** Users can be stuck on loading spinners indefinitely. Worse, the auth state is "limbo" — they appear authenticated to storage checks but not to context.

**Where:** [protected-route.jsx:36-76](file:///d:/Mallakhamb-Repo/Mallakhamb-server-refactor/Web/src/middleware/protected-route.jsx#L36-L76)

**How to fix:**
```jsx
import { isTokenExpired } from '@/utils/auth/tokenUtils';

// Inside ProtectedRoute, after getting token:
const token = secureStorage.getItem(`${storagePrefix}_token`);
const userData = secureStorage.getItem(`${storagePrefix}_user`);

// Add expiry check
if (token && isTokenExpired(token)) {
  secureStorage.removeItem(`${storagePrefix}_token`);
  secureStorage.removeItem(`${storagePrefix}_user`);
  return <Navigate to={loginPath} replace />;
}
```

