#### H-2: `getCurrentUserTypeFromURL()` Duplicated in 3 Places

**What:** The same URL-to-role mapping function exists in:
1. [App.jsx:20-28](file:///d:/Mallakhamb-Repo/Mallakhamb-server-refactor/Web/src/App.jsx#L20-L28)
2. [api-client.js:21-29](file:///d:/Mallakhamb-Repo/Mallakhamb-server-refactor/Web/src/services/api-client.js#L21-L29)
3. [protected-route.jsx:12-31](file:///d:/Mallakhamb-Repo/Mallakhamb-server-refactor/Web/src/middleware/protected-route.jsx#L12-L31)

**Why it matters:** If a new role is added (e.g., `organizer`), it must be updated in 3 places. The `/superadmin` vs `/admin` ordering matters and is easy to get wrong.

**How to fix:**
```js
// src/utils/auth/roleFromPath.js
const ROLE_PREFIXES = [
  { prefix: '/superadmin', role: 'superadmin' },
  { prefix: '/admin', role: 'admin' },
  { prefix: '/coach', role: 'coach' },
  { prefix: '/player', role: 'player' },
  { prefix: '/judge', role: 'judge' },
];

export const getRoleFromPath = (pathname) => {
  const match = ROLE_PREFIXES.find(({ prefix }) => pathname.startsWith(prefix));
  return match?.role ?? null;
};
```

