#### H-3: API Interceptor Uses `window.location.href` for Redirects

**What:** [api-client.js](file:///d:/Mallakhamb-Repo/Mallakhamb-server-refactor/Web/src/services/api-client.js#L62) uses `window.location.href = '/'` on 401/expired tokens. This causes a full page reload, destroying React state, triggering a re-download of all chunks, and losing any unsaved form data.

**Why it matters:** Poor UX — users filling out a long form hit a token expiry and lose everything. Also bypasses the safe redirect utility you built.

**Where:** Lines 62, 103, 125 in api-client.js

**How to fix:** Use a shared event emitter or auth context callback to navigate via React Router:

```js
// src/utils/auth/authEvents.js
export const authEvents = new EventTarget();
export const AUTH_EXPIRED = 'auth:expired';

// In api-client.js interceptor:
authEvents.dispatchEvent(new CustomEvent(AUTH_EXPIRED, { detail: { role: currentType } }));

// In App.jsx, listen:
useEffect(() => {
  const handler = (e) => {
    handleLogout(navigate);
  };
  authEvents.addEventListener(AUTH_EXPIRED, handler);
  return () => authEvents.removeEventListener(AUTH_EXPIRED, handler);
}, []);
```

