#### H-4: `secureStorage.clear()` Nukes All localStorage

**What:** [handleLogout](file:///d:/Mallakhamb-Repo/Mallakhamb-server-refactor/Web/src/App.jsx#L128-L130) calls `secureStorage.clear()` → `localStorage.clear()`, `localStorage.clear()` again, and `sessionStorage.clear()`. This wipes all storage including any third-party analytics data, user preferences, or other role sessions.

**Why it matters:** In a multi-role app where a user can be logged in as both `coach` and `admin` simultaneously, logging out as `coach` kills the `admin` session too.

**Where:** [App.jsx:128-131](file:///d:/Mallakhamb-Repo/Mallakhamb-server-refactor/Web/src/App.jsx#L128-L131)

**How to fix:**
```js
// Only remove keys for the current role
const handleLogout = async (navigate) => {
  const currentType = getCurrentUserTypeFromURL() || userType;
  // ...server logout call...
  
  // Targeted cleanup
  if (currentType) {
    secureStorage.removeItem(`${currentType}_token`);
    secureStorage.removeItem(`${currentType}_user`);
    secureStorage.removeItem(`${currentType}_current_competition`);
  }
  // Remove legacy keys
  localStorage.removeItem('token');
  localStorage.removeItem('user');
  localStorage.removeItem('userType');
  apiCache.clear();
  // ...
};
```

