#### M-6: `useApiCall` Hook Does Not Return Loading State

**What:** [useApiCall.js](file:///d:/Mallakhamb-Repo/Mallakhamb-server-refactor/Web/src/hooks/useApiCall.js) exposes `execute` and `executeWithLoading` but doesn't manage its own `loading`/`error` state. The JSDoc shows `loading` and `error` in the destructuring example but they're not returned.

**Why it matters:** Consumers must manage their own loading state, which defeats the purpose of a unified API call hook. The example in the JSDoc is misleading.

**Where:** [useApiCall.js:9-10](file:///d:/Mallakhamb-Repo/Mallakhamb-server-refactor/Web/src/hooks/useApiCall.js#L9-L10) vs [line 84-88](file:///d:/Mallakhamb-Repo/Mallakhamb-server-refactor/Web/src/hooks/useApiCall.js#L84-L88)

**How to fix:**
```js
export const useApiCall = () => {
  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(false);
  const [error, setError] = useState(null);
  
  const execute = useCallback(async (apiCall) => {
    setLoading(true);
    setError(null);
    try {
      const result = await apiCall();
      return result;
    } catch (err) {
      const msg = handleError(err);
      setError(msg);
      throw err;
    } finally {
      setLoading(false);
    }
  }, []);

  return { execute, loading, error, handleError };
};
```

