#### M-7: AuthContext Has No AuthProvider — Logic Lives in App.jsx

**What:** [AuthContext.jsx](file:///d:/Mallakhamb-Repo/Mallakhamb-server-refactor/Web/src/contexts/AuthContext.jsx) is just a `createContext` + `useAuth` hook. All auth logic (login, logout, storage, URL parsing) lives in [App.jsx:14-202](file:///d:/Mallakhamb-Repo/Mallakhamb-server-refactor/Web/src/App.jsx#L14-L202).

**Why it matters:** App.jsx is 216 lines with auth logic, URL detection, navbar visibility, and layout logic mixed together. This makes testing impossible (you can't test auth without rendering the entire app). `AppContent` has 3 `useEffect` hooks that all call `loadAuthData()` redundantly.

**How to fix:** Extract auth logic into an `AuthProvider`:

```jsx
// src/contexts/AuthProvider.jsx
export const AuthProvider = ({ children }) => {
  const [user, setUser] = useState(null);
  const [userType, setUserType] = useState(null);
  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(true);
  // ... all auth logic from App.jsx ...
  return (
    <AuthContext.Provider value={{ user, userType, loading, login, logout }}>
      {children}
    </AuthContext.Provider>
  );
};
```

