### Phase 3: Long-Term Architecture (1–2 months)

> [!NOTE]
> These are strategic improvements for scalability, testability, and security posture.

| # | Task | Rationale |
|---|------|-----------|
| 1 | **Move token storage to `httpOnly` cookies** | Eliminates entire class of XSS token-theft attacks. Requires server-side changes. |
| 2 | **Implement React Query (TanStack Query)** | Replace manual `useState`/`useEffect` data fetching with cache invalidation, background refetch, optimistic updates. Eliminates `apiCache.js` and most loading state management. |
| 3 | **Add production CSP with nonces** | Remove `unsafe-inline`/`unsafe-eval` by using Vite CSP plugin + server-side nonce injection. |
| 4 | **Add automated testing** | No tests exist. Add Vitest for hooks/utils, React Testing Library for components, Playwright for auth flows. |
| 5 | **Design system migration** | Complete the `DESIGN_TOKENS` migration. Remove deprecated `COLORS`/`ADMIN_COLORS` proxies. Convert all hardcoded color strings. |
| 6 | **TypeScript migration** | Gradual migration starting from `services/`, `hooks/`, and `utils/`. Prevents type mismatches (e.g., `user` being `null` vs `undefined`). |
| 7 | **Error boundary per route** | Wrap each route section in its own ErrorBoundary so a crash in judge scoring doesn't kill the admin dashboard. |
| 8 | **Bundle analysis** | Run `npx vite-bundle-visualizer` to find unexpected large chunks. The `AdminScoring.jsx` (42KB) and `AdminJudges.jsx` (41KB) files likely need component splitting. |
